1
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:48,520
What we are looking at now

2
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,580
is the lobby footage of Xinmai Hotel.

3
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:52,220
The deceased, Li Ting,

4
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:53,920
left on May 6

5
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:56,640
and didn't return until May 13.

6
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,780
This is the footage of his return.

7
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,400
Okay, next.

8
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,400
At 3:22 PM,

9
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:07,440
Li Ting returned to his room.

10
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,919
At this moment,

11
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,880
the cleaner was cleaning the room.

12
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:14,080
Li Ting asked the waiter to leave shortly after he went in.

13
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,850
This is the footage of him leaving.

14
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,640
Okay, next one.

15
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,120
After the waiter left,

16
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:28,280
at 4:14 PM,

17
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,880
he ordered a box of convenience food via delivery

18
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,680
and successfully signed for it.

19
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:33,480
After the deliveryman left,

20
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:35,040
he never stepped out of the room again.

21
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:37,480
No one else came during this period.

22
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,520
Until this morning,

23
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:42,760
which is May 26th at 8:03 AM,

24
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,680
when the waiter came to clean the room,

25
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,400
opened the door with a master key,

26
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,730
and found the deceased.

27
00:02:47,760 --> 00:02:49,560
No one went in or out.

28
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:52,360
Could there be a problem with the surveillance video?

29
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,520
The video has been authenticated.

30
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,320
There are no signs of tampering.

31
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,480
Good job, Fang.

32
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,360
Serve the people.

33
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:03,640
Could it be an accident?

34
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:08,480
Cheng Mo and I did a simulation analysis of the scene.

35
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:12,010
There's definitely something wrong with the state of the body.

36
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,160
Shao.

37
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:16,290
When will the autopsy report be ready?

38
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,400
The body is highly decomposed.

39
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,560
Plus, the temperature at the crime scene

40
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,640
was kept too low by the AC.

41
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:23,700
I can't give an accurate time of death report right now.

42
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,600
As soon as possible.

43
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,360
Okay.

44
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:28,200
Xiao Bai.

45
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,760
Do you have any new findings on your end?

46
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,520
The deceased's parents passed away early.

47
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,880
He has no relatives

48
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,200
or friends in Mancheng.

49
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,560
As a freelance writer,

50
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,680
the only person he interacts with

51
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,520
is the magazine editor.

52
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,680
The editor did contact him a few times,

53
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,600
but thought he was in a creative retreat

54
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,260
and didn't suspect anything.

55
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,079
Also, his wife, Lu Chen,

56
00:03:48,079 --> 00:03:50,480
separated from him half a year ago due to marital discord,

57
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,720
went back to her hometown in Luocheng,

58
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:53,640
and has been preparing for a divorce.

59
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:56,440
Li Ting went back to Luocheng on May 6th to discuss the divorce

60
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,120
and returned alone on the 13th.

61
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:00,480
Lu Chen obviously has an alibi.

62
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:04,050
They discussed divorce for a week.

63
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:09,760
Have Lu Chen come to the station as soon as possible.

64
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,720
I've already notified him.

65
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,800
He'll be here first thing tomorrow morning.

66
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,320
Strange.

67
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,760
What's strange?

68
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,959
No one entered or left the room.

69
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:22,320
Yet the victim was murdered.

70
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,680
This is a locked-room murder.

71
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,360
The waiter who found the deceased.

72
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,680
Where is the statement?

73
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,520
Oh.

74
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,360
She was terrified

75
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:33,040
and didn't have time to make a statement.

76
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,280
But I've already informed her.

77
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,480
She will be here soon.

78
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,840
Sister.

79
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,560
Sister Liu, don't be nervous.

80
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,120
We just want to ask you a few questions.

81
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,560
Just cooperate with the investigation.

82
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,120
Okay, I'll cooperate.

83
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,640
Li Ting, as a long-term tenant,

84
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,240
didn't leave his room for two weeks.

85
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,100
Didn't you want to go in and check?

86
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,440
We didn't go in.

87
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,080
He didn't leave his room for a while before.

88
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,880
The manager wanted to go in and check.

89
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,440
But he yelled at him.

90
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,880
And complained about us.

91
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,320
If we hadn't smelled the odor this time,

92
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,920
we wouldn't have gone in.

93
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,520
From May 13th to today,

94
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,600
have you noticed anything unusual?

95
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,840
Unusual?

96
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,320
A few days ago,

97
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:23,440
the staff break room on the first floor

98
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,280
smelled really bad.

99
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,780
I didn't pay much attention to it.

100
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,400
Now that I think about it,

101
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,640
it might have come from the second floor.

102
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,600
Which room?

103
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,170
I mean the staff break room.

104
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,120
Which room?

105
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:40,960
Oh.

106
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:43,159
Right below 208.

107
00:05:43,159 --> 00:05:44,240
Room 108.

108
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,800
Because it used to be the kitchen.

109
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:49,720
Later,

110
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,980
it was converted into a staff break room.

111
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,560
Why didn't you report the bad smell?

112
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,440
Xiao Zhao quit, didn't she?

113
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,760
She was in charge of the second floor.

114
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:02,440
I was in charge of the first floor and the staff break room.

115
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,760
Now that she's gone,

116
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,080
how can I manage?

117
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,920
Do you know why she quit?

118
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,920
I get angry just talking about it.

119
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:13,160
Isn't it because of Mr. Li in Room 208?

120
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,600
He insisted that Xiao Zhao stole his watch.

121
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:17,760
Zhao,

122
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:20,000
what's the rush?

123
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:23,000
The guest in 208 is saying I stole things again.

124
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,240
Still about that?

125
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,640
Yeah, it never ends.

126
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,000
I didn't steal anything.

127
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,560
It's endless.

128
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,520
Keep your voice down.

129
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,520
Why should I?

130
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,640
Is it fair to be treated like this?

131
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,720
Don't stoop to his level.

132
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,280
How can I not?

133
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,320
I'm really quitting.

134
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:35,760
Don't try to stop me.

135
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:36,360
Zhao.

136
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:38,400
Save your breath.

137
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,400
Zhao.

138
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,600
She was so angry.

139
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,800
She packed her bags and left that night.

140
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,840
Do you remember which day it was?

141
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:51,800
Yes.

142
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,520
Around 9 p.m. on the 13th.

143
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,040
Isn't that Zhao?

144
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,040
Zhao!

145
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,120
Zhao!

146
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,560
This kid...

147
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:09,440
She was in a hurry.

148
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:12,480
I called her several times, but she ignored me.

149
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:15,080
Young people nowadays just leave on a whim.

150
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,970
She must have felt wronged.

151
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,260
You guys order.

152
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,280
I'll do it.

153
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,600
I've been watching the surveillance footage all day.

154
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,130
My eyes are getting blurry,

155
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,560
but I still haven't found any useful clues.

156
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,960
As for this case,

157
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,960
it's most likely an accident.

158
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,400
Thank you for your hard work.

159
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,920
How about this?

160
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,640
Let's wait for my autopsy report first.

161
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,520
There might be other discoveries.

162
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:52,850
So when will your autopsy report be ready?

163
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,480
I promise it will be as soon as possible.

164
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,400
Two of these.

165
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,360
Thank you.

166
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,200
Hurry up, ma'am.

167
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:00,560
I'm starving. Thank you.

168
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,000
Got it.

169
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:01,600
Thank you.

170
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,580
Sit down. Hurry up and sit.

171
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,320
Sister.

172
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:10,180
Manager Feng sent over the information about the temporary cleaner.

173
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:11,760
Look.

174
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,880
I know her.

175
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,160
Isn't she the cleaner

176
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,280
who cleaned his room on the 13th?

177
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,530
Yes, that's her.

178
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:27,120
She even had an argument with the deceased.

179
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,120
According to Liu Ying,

180
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:33,440
it was because the deceased accused her of stealing that day.

181
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,320
That's right.

182
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,880
Then she must be the murderer.

183
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,880
Seeking revenge after being framed by the deceased.

184
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,880
Impossible.

185
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,809
I saw it very clearly on the surveillance.

186
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:46,480
The deceased was still alive when she left.

187
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:49,610
Then she must have entered the room using other methods.

188
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,290
What method?

189
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,600
What method?

190
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,840
For example,

191
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,200
she dropped a rope from the roof

192
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,480
and swung into the window.

193
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:03,480
This...

194
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,280
Are you out of your mind?

195
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,800
Have you been watching too many movies?

196
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,440
Female agent? Swinging in?

197
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,840
Then I'm the Monkey King.

198
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,800
Unbelievable.

199
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,720
Don't laugh at me.

200
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,520
She's right.

201
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,200
What?

202
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:16,120
Mr. Cheng thinks she's an agent too.

203
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:16,960
Not exactly.

204
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:19,120
There are no signs of forced entry on the window.

205
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,920
Then why did you say she's right?

206
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,360
I meant

207
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:26,480
the murderer definitely entered and exited the room in another way.

208
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:29,360
Could there be a secret passage?

209
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,570
She really is the talent you talked about.

210
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,160
Lao Zhang.

211
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:38,290
Why is your place leaking water again?

212
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,240
No way.

213
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,440
I just fixed it.

214
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,720
Go look, it's right in your kitchen.

215
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,560
It's so weird.

216
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,560
Every time my water pipe leaks,

217
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,490
how come you discover it before me?

218
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,720
Nonsense, I can't do business like this.

219
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,920
Fix it quickly.

220
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,280
Don't delay my business.

221
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:54,080
Come here.

222
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,360
I know.

223
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,960
A few days ago,

224
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,920
the staff lounge on the first floor

225
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:02,200
had a foul smell.

226
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,360
I didn't pay much attention to it then.

227
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:06,320
Now that I think about it,

228
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:10,080
it might have come from the second floor.

229
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
I know.

230
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,400
Cheng Mo.

231
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,260
Remember to get me an invoice.

232
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:21,640
Cheng Mo.

233
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,900
What's wrong with him?

234
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,920
Should we turn on the light first?

235
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,560
What are you looking for?

236
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:43,090
Do you remember Liu Ying's statement?

237
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,680
I remember.

238
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:48,560
She said when she was in the lounge,

239
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:51,240
she smelled something rotten.

240
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:58,520
The essence of a smell is tiny fragments of matter.

241
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:01,760
These fragments slowly diffuse,

242
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,020
and pass through here.

243
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,200
They continue to move in the air,

244
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:13,080
and finally reach the next floor.

245
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,690
So here is the question.

246
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,520
After Li Ting decayed,

247
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:22,320
how did these fragments float downstairs?

248
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,080
It seems Xiaobai was right.

249
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,320
There must be a secret passage here.

250
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,660
What are you doing?

251
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,400
Dong Shan, call the police quickly!

252
00:12:55,400 --> 00:12:56,200
No need.

253
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:59,120
Zhuang Lan, Accident Investigation Team.

254
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:01,920
We need a secondary investigation into the case.

255
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:03,960
Sorry,

256
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,080
Officer Zhuang Lan.

257
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,040
You see it's so dark,

258
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,040
and the lights aren't on.

259
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:08,920
We thought a thief had broken in.

260
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,040
Yes.

261
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,520
I understand.

262
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:13,880
But before the case is closed,

263
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,860
you can't just enter here freely.

264
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:16,560
Okay.

265
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:17,320
Understood.

266
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:17,640
Let's go, Dong Shan.

267
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:19,700
Call us anytime if you need anything.

268
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,640
This is the place.

269
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,040
Hey, Fang.

270
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,560
Major discovery.

271
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:14,600
San,

272
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:17,680
about what I asked you the other day,

273
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:18,520
is it true?

274
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:20,800
Okay.

275
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,040
Thank you.

276
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:22,960
Alright.

277
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,160
Yeah, I got it.
